cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.NE, cs.MM 

The paper deals with image processing and machine learning techniques for detecting buried targets using ground-penetrating radar data. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses feature learning approaches, which are commonly used in deep learning, indicating a possible fit with cs.LG (Machine Learning). The use of computerized algorithms for target detection suggests a possible fit with cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the use of radar data and signal processing techniques may also suggest a possible fit with cs.MM (Multimedia).
